WEBVTT

00:08.417 --> 00:10.375
Previously on "Homeland"...

00:10.375 --> 00:12.458
I'm not getting any better!

00:12.458 --> 00:14.959
Can't you get that
through your fuckin' skull?

00:14.959 --> 00:17.667
-Let me go.
-Let me go.

00:17.667 --> 00:18.500
[Conlin] Sekou is under arrest

00:18.500 --> 00:20.667
for material support
of terrorism.

00:20.667 --> 00:22.333
The government has offered
a plea bargain.

00:22.333 --> 00:24.000
But I'm not guilty.

00:24.000 --> 00:25.875
I'm not sure what he's done
is even illegal.

00:25.875 --> 00:27.291
[scoffs]
Do you keep photos of

00:27.291 --> 00:27.959
dead American soldiers
on your laptop?

00:27.959 --> 00:31.041
What I saw was an angry kid.

00:31.041 --> 00:32.708
-Who's down there?
-I told you. Peter Quinn.

00:32.708 --> 00:35.166
He's been in the hospital,

00:35.166 --> 00:36.000
and now he's with us
for a while.

00:36.000 --> 00:37.834
[Sekou] His name is Saad Mahsud.

00:37.834 --> 00:40.250
He's working for the FBI.

00:40.250 --> 00:42.625
Fucking Conlin, he doesn't care
about anything.

00:42.625 --> 00:44.500
All he keeps saying is just
get him to take the money.

00:44.500 --> 00:45.875
You can fix this.
You can tell the truth.

00:45.875 --> 00:48.667
You fucked up by coming here.

00:48.667 --> 00:50.583
[Clarence] You watch Clarice
don't run off with that now.

00:50.583 --> 00:51.708
[Clarice]
Oh, my God. It's a robbery!

00:51.708 --> 00:53.375
Nobody fucking move!

00:53.375 --> 00:55.333
[grunts]

00:55.333 --> 00:57.166
You think I'm advising the next
President of the United States?

00:57.166 --> 00:59.250
I think her entire
national security platform

00:59.250 --> 01:02.041
came right out of
that head of yours.

01:02.041 --> 01:03.708
We have intel
from our partners

01:03.708 --> 01:06.208
that the Iranians are cheating
on the nuclear deal.

01:06.208 --> 01:08.208
There's an Iranian bag man,
Farhad Nafisi.

01:08.208 --> 01:10.750
The Israelis are gonna
pick him up.

01:10.750 --> 01:13.375
Dar told me they have evidence
of a parallel program

01:13.375 --> 01:15.542
with North Korea.
-Mossad can't be trusted

01:15.542 --> 01:17.208
to be even remotely objective
on this.

01:17.208 --> 01:20.291
-What do you suggest?
-Saul Berenson.

01:20.291 --> 01:23.375
The nuclear arrangement started
with Saul. He wants it to work.

01:23.375 --> 01:26.417
You're going to Abu Dhabi.
The Mossad Operation.

01:26.417 --> 01:29.083
You've really
never seen this?

01:30.583 --> 01:31.750
[grunts]

01:31.750 --> 01:35.458
[exhales deeply]

01:39.166 --> 01:41.083
♪ And the home ♪

01:41.083 --> 01:44.750
♪ Of the brave ♪

01:44.750 --> 01:48.125
♪♪♪

01:48.125 --> 01:50.750
[Scott-Heron]
The first revolution

01:50.750 --> 01:53.917
is when you change your mind
about how you look at things

01:53.917 --> 01:56.542
and see that there might be
another way to look at it

01:56.542 --> 01:57.959
that you have not been shown.

01:57.959 --> 01:59.000
[crowd shouting]

01:59.000 --> 02:01.375
[Scahill] The brutality
against protesters,

02:01.375 --> 02:03.625
the para-militarization
of law enforcement.

02:03.625 --> 02:05.792
[Carrie] That's why
we have to keep trying.

02:05.792 --> 02:07.375
[PE] We don't need a police
state in this country

02:07.375 --> 02:09.458
to fight terrorism,
we need a new strategy.

02:09.458 --> 02:13.166
[Gil Scott-Heron] The revolution
will not be televised.

02:13.166 --> 02:14.542
[Greenwald] ...the system
of indefinite detention...

02:14.542 --> 02:16.625
[Scahill] FBI and the CIA
targeting Muslim communities...

02:16.625 --> 02:19.625
[DeMarco] Security. Got an
agitated non-compliant patient.

02:19.625 --> 02:20.625
Get away from me!

02:20.625 --> 02:22.792
-What's his name again?
-Peter Quinn.

02:22.792 --> 02:24.625
[Scott-Heron] You will not be
able to stay home, brother.

02:24.625 --> 02:28.083
You will not be able to
plug in, turn on, and cop out.

02:28.083 --> 02:29.792
-It's a very alarming charge.
-The Russians

02:29.792 --> 02:31.250
hacked our committees.

02:31.250 --> 02:33.458
[woman] The continuation
of endless war.

02:33.458 --> 02:36.000
[Quinn] Can't you get that
through your fucking skull?

02:36.000 --> 02:38.333
[Scott-Heron] The revolution

02:38.333 --> 02:40.125
will put you
in the driver's seat.

02:40.125 --> 02:42.083
[Scahill]
The US continues to engage

02:42.083 --> 02:43.458
in a covert war
with very, very high stakes.

02:43.458 --> 02:46.792
[Saul] I made promises
and didn't keep them.

02:48.333 --> 02:50.875
[Priest] This world began
right after 9/11.

02:52.542 --> 02:55.041
[Scott-Heron] The revolution
will not be televised,

02:55.041 --> 02:57.000
not be televised.
There will be no rerun,

02:57.000 --> 03:00.458
brothers and sisters.
The revolution will be live.

03:00.458 --> 03:02.000
[Chaffetz] Which agency?

03:02.000 --> 03:04.834
[McCullough] I can't say that
here in an open hearing, sir.

03:04.834 --> 03:06.083
[Quinn] You saved me.

03:06.083 --> 03:08.166
[Carrie] Yes.

03:08.166 --> 03:08.500
[Quinn] Why?

03:30.250 --> 03:31.542
[switch clicks]

03:36.083 --> 03:36.542
[shirt thuds]

03:45.708 --> 03:47.875
[grunts]

03:50.875 --> 03:54.542
[faucet squeaks]

03:54.542 --> 03:57.375
[gas hissing]

04:04.375 --> 04:06.000
[door rattles]

04:06.000 --> 04:07.708
[exhaling sharply]

04:07.708 --> 04:10.625
[grunting]

04:10.625 --> 04:11.041
[hissing continues]

04:11.041 --> 04:14.750
[gagging]

04:17.083 --> 04:19.375
[screaming]

04:19.375 --> 04:23.667
-[continues screaming]
-Quinn. Quinn. Quinn!

04:23.667 --> 04:24.542
Quinn, it's me.

04:24.542 --> 04:28.125
-[continues screaming]
-Quinn. Shh.

04:28.125 --> 04:30.667
-It's me. It's Carrie.
-[breathing heavily]

04:30.667 --> 04:34.333
You're okay. You're okay.
You're in my house.

04:34.333 --> 04:36.083
You're safe. You're safe.

04:36.083 --> 04:39.625
[breathing heavily]

04:39.625 --> 04:42.792
Shh.

04:42.792 --> 04:44.500
[exhales deeply]

04:47.083 --> 04:49.959
That must be some dream.

04:49.959 --> 04:52.291
[exhales deeply]

04:52.291 --> 04:54.333
[inhales deeply]

04:54.333 --> 04:58.458
[breathing deeply]

05:02.458 --> 05:03.875
Just breathe.

05:05.291 --> 05:06.959
[breathing deeply]

05:06.959 --> 05:08.959
[inhales deeply]

05:08.959 --> 05:11.542
[exhales deeply]

05:15.125 --> 05:17.750
Quinn, no. Quinn, no.

05:17.750 --> 05:19.917
Hey, come on, Quinn!
What are you doing?

05:21.291 --> 05:24.000
[exhales deeply]

05:24.000 --> 05:25.041
I-I thought you were--

05:25.041 --> 05:28.125
No, I wasn't. [scoffs]

05:28.125 --> 05:30.041
Oh, shit.

05:30.041 --> 05:31.792
[Franny] Mommy?

05:33.375 --> 05:36.792
Hey, sweetheart?
Go back upstairs, okay?

05:36.792 --> 05:37.583
Go on. Mommy will be
right there.

05:40.000 --> 05:43.500
[ascending footsteps]

05:52.000 --> 05:55.542
Okay. Quinn...

05:55.542 --> 05:58.583
You're coming down from
a lot of medication. I get that.

05:58.583 --> 06:00.667
But if you're gonna be
living in my home

06:00.667 --> 06:03.000
with me and my daughter...

06:08.708 --> 06:10.000
[cellphone vibrates]

06:10.000 --> 06:13.125
[vibrating]

06:13.125 --> 06:16.125
-I'm gonna be out all day.
[cellphone continues vibrating]

06:16.125 --> 06:19.083
Uh...Franny's gonna go
with her nanny after school.

06:19.083 --> 06:23.875
-Should I call Max to--
-I don't need a babysitter.

06:23.875 --> 06:25.834
[vibrating continues]

06:25.834 --> 06:27.166
-Fine.
[cellphone clicks]

06:27.166 --> 06:28.625
Reda?

06:28.625 --> 06:30.375
I need you in the office now.

06:30.375 --> 06:32.417
-What's goin' on?
-Conlin just called

06:32.417 --> 06:35.041
to ask why the hell you were
harassing his informant.

06:35.041 --> 06:36.834
I expected him to report
the meeting.

06:36.834 --> 06:39.875
Which is why you should've
avoided him in the first place.

06:39.875 --> 06:41.000
When can you be here?

06:41.000 --> 06:42.792
Uh, soon as I get Franny
to school.

06:42.792 --> 06:43.917
As fast as you can.

06:43.917 --> 06:44.875
[receiver thuds]

06:44.875 --> 06:47.542
-[sighs, whispers] Fuck.
[cellphone clicks]

06:47.542 --> 06:50.625
[engine revving]

06:53.208 --> 06:55.375
They're still with us.

06:55.375 --> 06:56.458
Police?

06:56.458 --> 06:58.917
-No. SSD.
-Lose 'em.

07:06.041 --> 07:08.708
[tires screeching]

07:12.291 --> 07:16.208
♪ suspenseful music ♪

07:18.166 --> 07:21.291
[engines revving]

07:23.166 --> 07:25.542
How we doin'?

07:25.542 --> 07:26.834
Still there.

07:26.834 --> 07:30.625
♪♪♪

07:30.625 --> 07:34.750
[tires screeching]

07:39.792 --> 07:40.333
[tires screech]

07:40.333 --> 07:42.750
-Ready?
-Ready.

07:43.792 --> 07:46.500
[brakes squeal,
indistinct conversations]

07:49.667 --> 07:51.333
[engine revving]

07:51.333 --> 07:55.250
[indistinct conversations]

08:00.291 --> 08:03.375
♪♪♪

08:09.667 --> 08:11.834
Mr. Greenburg?

08:11.834 --> 08:15.250
[engine idling]

08:20.417 --> 08:24.417
[indistinct conversations
continue]

08:29.041 --> 08:32.417
Hold on.

08:32.417 --> 08:34.625
[engine revs]

08:34.625 --> 08:36.417
[indistinct conversations]
-[sighs]

08:36.417 --> 08:37.792
[Reda] Hey, you called me.

08:37.792 --> 08:39.750
I'm just having
an honest reaction here.

08:39.750 --> 08:41.542
And no, it isn't
business as usual.

08:41.542 --> 08:43.500
I'm gonna fight you on this.
Goodbye.

08:43.500 --> 08:45.708
[receiver thuds]
-Who was that?

08:45.708 --> 08:48.458
Ortiz. They're withdrawing
the plea deal.

08:48.458 --> 08:50.333
-What?
-Yeah, we're going to trial.

08:50.333 --> 08:52.458
And that means
Sekou's looking at 15 years

08:52.458 --> 08:54.250
-in a Federal Supermax.
-Come on, Reda.

08:54.250 --> 08:57.000
-They can't do that, can they?
-Withdraw the plea deal?

08:57.000 --> 08:59.041
Sure they can,
given sufficient grounds.

08:59.041 --> 09:00.792
And defying a court order
on an issue

09:00.792 --> 09:04.000
of national security
is plenty sufficient.

09:04.000 --> 09:05.458
There must be some way
to fight this.

09:05.458 --> 09:08.083
How 'bout going back
to the judge?

09:08.083 --> 09:09.708
It was her order you defied,
Carrie.

09:09.708 --> 09:12.417
I hardly think we'll get
a friendly audience there.

09:12.417 --> 09:14.083
But Saad told the FBI
to back off.

09:14.083 --> 09:16.041
He told them that Sekou
was no threat.

09:16.041 --> 09:19.208
They practically had to shove
the five grand down his throat,

09:19.208 --> 09:21.542
for Chrissake! I mean,
surely, we can use that.

09:21.542 --> 09:24.208
How? By putting you on
the stand? Last time I checked,

09:24.208 --> 09:26.542
you were still a member
of the defense team.

09:26.542 --> 09:28.708
Simone was there, too.
She heard everything.

09:28.708 --> 09:31.875
She's the defendant's sister.
Not a credible witness either.

09:31.875 --> 09:33.834
[sighs]

09:35.667 --> 09:37.959
This isn't the arrangement
we made, Carrie.

09:37.959 --> 09:39.792
-What do you mean?
-Our partnership.

09:39.792 --> 09:41.708
You were supposed
to secure funding,

09:41.708 --> 09:44.250
investigate, advise.
What you weren't supposed to do

09:44.250 --> 09:45.125
was take matters
into your own hands,

09:45.125 --> 09:47.417
break the law.

09:47.417 --> 09:50.291
-I'm sorry, Reda. I fucked up.
-Yeah.

09:50.291 --> 09:52.583
You did.

09:56.750 --> 09:58.667
-Where you going?
-Downtown to the MDC

09:58.667 --> 10:01.959
to tell Sekou what's going on.
-No, I'll do it.

10:01.959 --> 10:03.667
That's not necessary.

10:03.667 --> 10:05.792
No. It's my fault.
I'll tell him.

10:16.166 --> 10:20.125
[engine rumbling]

10:20.125 --> 10:23.041
[indistinct conversations]

10:26.291 --> 10:30.125
[engine revving]

10:32.708 --> 10:35.417
♪ jazzy music ♪

10:35.417 --> 10:39.166
[woman singing
in foreign language]

10:39.166 --> 10:40.959
[doorbell rings]

10:40.959 --> 10:43.792
♪♪♪

10:51.458 --> 10:53.208
[door creaks]

10:57.792 --> 10:59.125
[door closes]

11:00.792 --> 11:02.125
This yours?

11:02.125 --> 11:04.417
I share it
with a girlfriend.

11:04.417 --> 11:06.375
Very nice.

11:06.375 --> 11:07.917
-Business is good.
-[chuckles]

11:07.917 --> 11:09.291
You can leave your money
over there.

11:09.291 --> 11:15.125
♪♪♪

11:16.250 --> 11:18.291
Here.

11:18.291 --> 11:20.208
♪♪♪

11:20.208 --> 11:22.750
[inhales slowly]

11:22.750 --> 11:25.125
[exhales slowly]

11:25.125 --> 11:28.834
♪♪♪

11:28.834 --> 11:30.333
Come on.

11:30.333 --> 11:32.708
There's a killer view
from the bedroom window.

11:34.583 --> 11:35.417
[sighs contentedly]

11:35.417 --> 11:39.500
[door rattles]

11:39.500 --> 11:41.083
What is this?

11:47.333 --> 11:48.834
[punch lands]
-[Nafisi grunts]

11:48.834 --> 11:51.375
[coughs]

11:51.375 --> 11:53.917
[gasps sharply]

11:53.917 --> 11:57.500
[grunting]

11:57.500 --> 12:00.792
[coughs]

12:00.792 --> 12:02.041
[wheezes]

12:02.041 --> 12:05.208
[coughing]

12:06.917 --> 12:08.041
[wheezing]

12:08.041 --> 12:11.875
Don't try to talk. You won't
be able to for a while.

12:11.875 --> 12:14.166
Probably a good thing, too.

12:14.166 --> 12:17.417
That way, we can skip
all the formalities.

12:17.417 --> 12:19.041
You know, demanding to speak
to your consul,

12:19.041 --> 12:23.500
threatening a grave
diplomatic incident, et cetera.

12:23.500 --> 12:27.917
You are Farhad Nafisi, a member
of the Iranian delegation

12:27.917 --> 12:29.750
to the Ninth International
Conference

12:29.750 --> 12:32.166
on Applied Aerospace Science
and Technology.

12:32.166 --> 12:35.083
Not your only reason
for being here, though.

12:35.083 --> 12:37.750
In fact, you've attended
very little of the conference.

12:37.750 --> 12:40.291
Truth is,
your main purpose here

12:40.291 --> 12:42.708
is to negotiate
an illegal arms deal

12:42.708 --> 12:46.250
on behalf of the Iranian
Revolutionary Guard Corps...

12:46.250 --> 12:50.708
with a little personal business
on the side.

12:50.708 --> 12:53.625
[pictures rustling]

12:58.166 --> 13:00.667
I understand, believe me.

13:00.667 --> 13:02.625
I can only imagine how dismally
these would be viewed

13:02.625 --> 13:07.000
by your superiors
back in Tehran,

13:07.000 --> 13:07.959
especially when
it's revealed to them

13:07.959 --> 13:10.000
that your little Mina
is actually Mossad.

13:16.333 --> 13:19.125
At best, your career as
a government official is over.

13:19.125 --> 13:22.667
At worst...well,
you know better than I do.

13:22.667 --> 13:25.166
Let's just say certain organs
of State Security

13:25.166 --> 13:26.708
would be involved.

13:26.708 --> 13:29.417
Mm.

13:30.417 --> 13:33.291
What do you want?

13:33.291 --> 13:36.667
I want you to think about
everything I've said.

13:36.667 --> 13:38.959
Catch your breath.

13:38.959 --> 13:43.500
In five minutes or so,
we'll be into your phone.

13:44.583 --> 13:46.125
I'll be back then.

13:46.125 --> 13:47.291
[chair scrapes floor]

13:51.417 --> 13:53.667
[door opens]

13:53.667 --> 13:56.000
-[sighs]
[door closes]

13:56.000 --> 13:59.208
[Tovah] The Iranian delegation
does everything in groups.

13:59.208 --> 14:03.708
Eat in groups, shop in groups,
go for walks in groups.

14:03.708 --> 14:07.333
Not Nafisi. He's different.

14:07.333 --> 14:09.542
He holds himself apart.

14:09.542 --> 14:12.291
Dines alone,
walks the beach alone.

14:12.291 --> 14:15.041
Plus, he gets here two days
after the others.

14:15.041 --> 14:17.000
Presumably on the heels of
his alleged trip to North Korea.

14:17.000 --> 14:20.625
Nothing "alleged" about it.
We have footage of him

14:20.625 --> 14:22.375
boarding a private plane
in Tehran,

14:22.375 --> 14:24.542
which was then tracked
to Samjiyon Airbase.

14:24.542 --> 14:26.542
With a refueling stop
in southern Russia.

14:26.542 --> 14:28.291
And I understand
a change of aircraft.

14:28.291 --> 14:30.583
You don't really know if he got
as far as North Korea, do you?

14:30.583 --> 14:33.333
It's the logical conclusion.

14:33.333 --> 14:35.417
I'm not here to draw
conclusions. I'm here

14:35.417 --> 14:39.208
to find objective evidence
of a parallel nuclear program.

14:39.208 --> 14:41.917
Forgive me, but I have doubts
about your objectivity.

14:41.917 --> 14:44.166
Everyone knows you support
a deal with Iran.

14:44.166 --> 14:47.375
Just as everyone knows
you're already convinced

14:47.375 --> 14:48.708
they're cheating on it.

14:54.417 --> 14:56.000
[buzzer, door opens]

14:59.083 --> 15:00.000
[door closes]

15:05.083 --> 15:06.000
[buzzer, door unlocks]

15:11.750 --> 15:12.583
Where's my lawyer?

15:12.583 --> 15:14.000
Where's Mr. Hashem?

15:14.000 --> 15:17.208
I need to talk to you
about something.

15:21.333 --> 15:22.625
[sighs]

15:22.625 --> 15:24.125
[chair scrapes floor]

15:26.500 --> 15:29.083
[chair clatters]

15:29.083 --> 15:30.917
Sekou, do you remember
the judge

15:30.917 --> 15:34.041
who ordered us
to stay away from Saad?

15:34.041 --> 15:35.667
Yeah. So?

15:40.000 --> 15:44.417
I disobeyed the judge's order.
I found Saad.

15:44.417 --> 15:45.959
Why?

15:45.959 --> 15:49.333
I thought I could make him admit
something that would help us.

15:49.333 --> 15:50.583
Did he?

15:50.583 --> 15:52.708
Yes.

15:52.708 --> 15:54.291
But we can't use it.

15:55.000 --> 15:58.583
And he reported me to the FBI.

15:58.583 --> 16:00.583
And as a consequence,

16:00.583 --> 16:03.458
the government has withdrawn
your plea offer.

16:03.458 --> 16:04.166
I'm sorry.

16:07.708 --> 16:10.458
I wasn't interested in
their offer anyway.

16:10.458 --> 16:13.083
Seven years? [chuckles]
Forget that.

16:15.708 --> 16:17.959
I don't think you understand.

16:17.959 --> 16:20.291
Understand what?

16:20.291 --> 16:21.583
Where's Mr. Hashem?

16:21.583 --> 16:23.708
Sekou, just --
just listen, okay?

16:23.708 --> 16:26.041
There is no more plea offer.

16:26.041 --> 16:28.959
Not for seven years,
not for three.

16:28.959 --> 16:33.000
The government has decided
to take your case to trial.

16:33.000 --> 16:34.625
But we can't go to trial.

16:34.625 --> 16:37.166
Mr. Hashem said
that would be a mistake.

16:37.166 --> 16:38.083
Yeah, I know what he said.

16:38.083 --> 16:40.834
Yeah, he said I could get
15 years.

16:40.834 --> 16:43.208
The thing is, we don't have
a choice anymore.

16:45.625 --> 16:48.166
Well, then, tell them that
I'll take the plea.

16:48.166 --> 16:51.625
Tell them I will take
the seven years. Just tell them.

16:51.625 --> 16:56.375
It's no longer an option.
I defied a court order.

16:56.375 --> 16:56.875
I am s--

16:56.875 --> 17:00.041
I am so, so sorry.

17:00.041 --> 17:02.083
You're sorry?

17:02.083 --> 17:04.083
I could be 40 years old
before I get outta here!

17:04.083 --> 17:06.250
Look, I will find a way
to fix this.

17:06.250 --> 17:10.000
[slams table]
-What are you talkin' about?!

17:10.000 --> 17:12.583
-Somebody! Get me out of here!
-Hey. I promise you --

17:12.583 --> 17:14.708
Help!
Get your hands off of me!

17:14.708 --> 17:16.291
[buzzer, door unlocks]

17:18.875 --> 17:20.750
How could you do this to me?

17:25.375 --> 17:28.250
♪ melancholy music ♪

17:32.542 --> 17:33.458
[door closes]

17:37.708 --> 17:40.583
Feeling better, I hope. You
gonna tell me about

17:40.583 --> 17:43.375
your dealings with First
Emirates Bank here in Abu Dhabi?

17:46.166 --> 17:47.458
[speaks Farsi]

17:47.458 --> 17:49.166
Joseph.

17:52.875 --> 17:54.500
Open your eye.

17:54.500 --> 17:56.458
-[grunting]
-Open it. Open it wide.

17:56.458 --> 17:59.083
-Open it. There you go.
-[grunts]

17:59.083 --> 18:02.000
[click, beep]
-[Saul] Got it.

18:02.000 --> 18:03.417
Good.

18:16.875 --> 18:19.166
Says here you have
$120 million line of credit

18:19.166 --> 18:20.417
at First Emirates,

18:20.417 --> 18:23.875
Little over half of which was
accessed in the last week.

18:26.291 --> 18:27.542
So?

18:27.542 --> 18:29.959
Compliant banks,
correspondent accounts,

18:29.959 --> 18:33.000
these are the same tactics used
to counter UN sanctions,

18:33.000 --> 18:33.917
fund Hezbollah,
export your revolution

18:33.917 --> 18:36.041
to the rest of the world.

18:36.041 --> 18:37.208
Is that a compliment?

18:40.583 --> 18:41.291
[lighter clicks,
cellphone thuds]

18:44.750 --> 18:45.667
What's the money for
this time?

18:45.667 --> 18:48.000
[exhales]

18:51.792 --> 18:54.959
You're not Israeli, are you?
You're American.

18:54.959 --> 18:56.834
Answer the question.

18:56.834 --> 19:00.542
But I thought
we were friends now.

19:00.542 --> 19:02.458
Friends don't sponsor terrorism.
What's the money for?

19:09.875 --> 19:11.834
A down payment on a delivery

19:11.834 --> 19:14.625
of Russian anti-aircraft
batteries.

19:14.625 --> 19:17.166
-[Saul] S-400?
-[Nafisi] You've heard of her?

19:17.166 --> 19:20.291
Well, of course you have.
She's a beast, no?

19:20.291 --> 19:23.125
Not scheduled for deployment
till late next year.

19:23.125 --> 19:26.166
Yeah.
We're getting ours early.

19:30.458 --> 19:32.583
How'd you swing that?

19:32.583 --> 19:35.667
Apparently, Mr. Putin
believes in discouraging

19:35.667 --> 19:40.291
our Zionist neighbors from
starting the next World War.

19:40.291 --> 19:42.291
I hope they're listening.

19:42.291 --> 19:44.291
First Emirates Bank
is a known facilitator

19:44.291 --> 19:47.792
for countries trying to sell
parts and technology

19:47.792 --> 19:49.667
tied to
nuclear weapon systems.

19:49.667 --> 19:51.500
Ah.

19:52.917 --> 19:55.792
So that's what all this
is about?

19:55.792 --> 19:58.417
Well, that and your recent trip
to Samjiyon Airbase.

19:58.417 --> 20:00.166
[chuckles]

20:00.166 --> 20:03.250
Excuse me, but no.
Now you've got the wrong man.

20:03.250 --> 20:05.500
I've never been
to North Korea.

20:08.917 --> 20:12.041
You landed in Irkutsk first,

20:12.041 --> 20:13.917
then onward
in a different plane

20:13.917 --> 20:15.375
to Samjiyon.

20:15.375 --> 20:18.125
I was in Irkutsk to meet
with Kremlin officials.

20:18.125 --> 20:21.583
It's where the S-400
is manufactured,

20:21.583 --> 20:24.041
for your information.
-And after that, you went

20:24.041 --> 20:25.708
to North Korea to discuss
a parallel program there.

20:25.708 --> 20:30.250
Fantasy. You -- you have
no evidence of this whatsoever.

20:30.250 --> 20:32.542
What's the range
of the S-400?

20:34.083 --> 20:36.458
More than 250 miles.

20:36.458 --> 20:38.708
-Up to what altitudes?
-[Nafisi] 90,000 feet.

20:38.708 --> 20:41.000
How many targets can it track
simultaneously?

20:41.000 --> 20:44.708
300, with the ability
to engage 36 of them

20:44.708 --> 20:46.792
at any one time.

20:59.083 --> 21:01.083
[photographs rustle]

21:08.083 --> 21:11.708
I'm...I'm free to go?

21:11.708 --> 21:13.959
You can go,
but you're not free.

21:13.959 --> 21:15.875
[Saul] Copies
of these photographs

21:15.875 --> 21:19.250
can be e-mailed to everyone on
your contact list at any time.

21:19.250 --> 21:21.041
Understood?

21:27.583 --> 21:29.458
Something you should know.

21:32.291 --> 21:33.667
What?

21:35.959 --> 21:38.041
Iran doesn't want
a nuclear weapon.

21:38.041 --> 21:40.542
It never did.

21:40.542 --> 21:42.959
-Nonsense.
-It's true.

21:42.959 --> 21:45.125
Three decades of sanctions
were killing us.

21:45.125 --> 21:47.792
We had to find a way
to get them lifted.

21:47.792 --> 21:50.333
So we started spinning
centrifuges.

21:50.333 --> 21:52.417
That got some attention.

21:52.417 --> 21:55.375
So we spun some more.
Even more attention.

21:55.375 --> 21:58.291
In the end,
all we had to do

21:58.291 --> 22:00.917
was negotiate away
a program

22:00.917 --> 22:03.417
we never wanted
in the first place.

22:08.125 --> 22:12.250
We'll be in touch,
Mr. Nafisi.

22:21.708 --> 22:22.917
[door slams]

22:24.166 --> 22:25.500
What are you doing?

22:25.500 --> 22:27.041
-You're letting him go?
-I am.

22:27.041 --> 22:29.166
You believe that bullshit
for one minute?

22:29.166 --> 22:31.083
-I didn't. No.
-I don't understand.

22:31.083 --> 22:34.166
The S-400 is classified
as a defensive weapon.

22:34.166 --> 22:36.750
Iran has every right to buy it
under the agreement.

22:38.208 --> 22:40.834
So why is Nafisi drawing funds
from a covert account

22:40.834 --> 22:42.291
to pay for it?

22:42.291 --> 22:43.875
-Exactly.
-[sighs]

22:43.875 --> 22:45.166
Far more likely,
he's transferring the funds

22:45.166 --> 22:47.667
directly to the North Koreans,

22:47.667 --> 22:52.166
who also use First Emirates as
their bank of choice in the UAE.

22:52.166 --> 22:54.375
And you will
tell Dar Adal this?

22:54.375 --> 22:56.417
I will.

22:56.417 --> 22:57.708
Thank you.

22:57.708 --> 23:00.667
You must be gratified.

23:00.667 --> 23:01.750
And you're disappointed.

23:01.750 --> 23:05.125
Just because I believe in
the merits of the deal

23:05.125 --> 23:06.792
doesn't mean
I'm any less concerned

23:06.792 --> 23:09.583
about Iran cheating on it.

23:14.583 --> 23:18.083
[distant clanking]

23:25.041 --> 23:26.583
[electricity crackles]

23:26.583 --> 23:28.917
[distant thud]

23:28.917 --> 23:30.959
[crackling stops]

23:37.041 --> 23:39.333
[exhales sharply]

23:39.333 --> 23:41.708
[rumbling]

23:41.708 --> 23:44.959
[object rolls, thud]

23:50.083 --> 23:52.208
[blade zings]

23:53.250 --> 23:56.375
♪ suspenseful music ♪

24:11.291 --> 24:14.625
[floorboards creaking]

24:14.625 --> 24:18.250
[footsteps]

24:21.083 --> 24:22.708
[lock clicks]

24:24.625 --> 24:27.291
[clicking]

24:27.291 --> 24:31.500
[clicking continues]

24:31.500 --> 24:35.458
♪♪♪

24:35.458 --> 24:37.291
[door closes in distance]

24:37.291 --> 24:40.375
♪♪♪

24:58.375 --> 25:01.834
♪♪♪

25:09.834 --> 25:12.667
♪♪♪

25:22.917 --> 25:26.166
Then it's as we feared?
A parallel program?

25:26.166 --> 25:27.917
[cellphone beeps]
-[Saul] Well...

25:27.917 --> 25:29.708
it was complicated.

25:29.708 --> 25:32.458
I don't understand.
You didn't break him?

25:32.458 --> 25:33.625
He was IRGC-trained.

25:33.625 --> 25:36.000
Breaking would have taken days.
We had hours.

25:36.000 --> 25:37.959
Who did the interview?

25:37.959 --> 25:39.000
[Saul] I just told you, I did.

25:39.000 --> 25:41.708
Goddamn it, Saul. You should've
put Tovah on him.

25:41.708 --> 25:45.542
It was her operation.
She made the call.

25:45.542 --> 25:47.375
Well, what do I tell
the President?

25:47.375 --> 25:48.417
What do I tell Keane?

25:48.417 --> 25:51.125
Just thinking about that.

25:51.125 --> 25:52.500
It's déjà vu, Dar.

25:52.500 --> 25:54.625
-We've been here before.
-What do you mean?

25:54.625 --> 25:57.625
Well, the last time
we were wrong about WMDs,

25:57.625 --> 25:59.834
turned into
a national nightmare.

25:59.834 --> 26:01.834
Are we wrong here?

26:01.834 --> 26:04.542
No, I don't think so,
but...

26:04.542 --> 26:06.708
I didn't think so
then either.

26:06.708 --> 26:09.708
-Sorry to interrupt.
-Listen, I gotta go.

26:09.708 --> 26:11.041
I'll write up the report
on the flight home.

26:11.041 --> 26:13.250
[Dar] Good.

26:13.250 --> 26:16.208
I just needed the folder,
Mr. Greenburg. For the shredder.

26:16.208 --> 26:17.125
Oh, no worries.
I can do it.

26:17.125 --> 26:19.834
-You sure?
-Truth is, I love to shred.

26:21.959 --> 26:24.417
[indistinct conversations,
folder clatters]

26:29.208 --> 26:32.291
[whirring]

26:35.417 --> 26:39.250
[whirring continues]

26:39.250 --> 26:43.083
♪♪♪

26:59.875 --> 27:03.083
[whirring resumes]

27:03.083 --> 27:05.959
[insects chirping]

27:17.375 --> 27:19.708
[engine turns off]

27:22.458 --> 27:24.291
[switch clicks]
-[woman] Come on, guys.

27:24.291 --> 27:27.041
[car door closes, switch clicks]
-[woman] Watch yourself.

27:28.708 --> 27:31.500
Honey, uh, take the boys inside.
I'll be in, in a sec, huh?

27:31.500 --> 27:32.792
[woman] All right.

27:45.000 --> 27:47.625
[house door opens]
-Hey, Roger.

27:47.625 --> 27:50.083
Christ, Carrie.
You should've called first.

27:50.083 --> 27:51.667
Old habits.

27:51.667 --> 27:53.250
This is my home.

27:57.000 --> 27:59.500
-I need a favor.
-Of course you do.

27:59.500 --> 28:01.834
I need the transcript of a call
placed between these two numbers

28:01.834 --> 28:04.583
within 24 hours of this date.
-No way.

28:04.583 --> 28:07.083
Just listen.

28:07.083 --> 28:09.000
This is a call between
an FBI agent and his informant.

28:09.000 --> 28:12.333
-Definitely no way.
-Discussing a kid I represent.

28:12.333 --> 28:14.750
The government's saying
he's a terrorist. He's not.

28:14.750 --> 28:16.875
First of all, we --
we don't have access

28:16.875 --> 28:18.583
to actual conversations,
just a record of their calls.

28:18.583 --> 28:22.333
-Oh, please.
-Even if we did,

28:22.333 --> 28:24.959
this is the kind of thing
that kills careers.

28:26.667 --> 28:29.875
I shouldn't even be
talking to you.

28:29.875 --> 28:32.708
Come on, Roger. We went out
on some limbs for each other,

28:32.708 --> 28:34.959
way out on some limbs.
-It's different now.

28:34.959 --> 28:36.291
Look, this isn't Baghdad.

28:36.291 --> 28:38.208
Please. I fucked up
this kid's life.

28:38.208 --> 28:40.208
He could get sent away
for 15 years.

28:40.208 --> 28:42.792
I'm sorry. I can't.

28:45.208 --> 28:47.041
Bye, Carrie.

28:47.041 --> 28:49.542
I'm gonna text you
those numbers anyway.

28:52.375 --> 28:55.542
♪ melancholy music ♪

29:03.166 --> 29:05.417
[house door closes]

29:05.417 --> 29:08.750
[indistinct conversations]

29:08.750 --> 29:12.667
[Dar] Saul,
where the hell are you?

29:12.667 --> 29:13.917
About to cross into
the West Bank, actually.

29:13.917 --> 29:16.625
What happened?
Why the change of plan?

29:16.625 --> 29:17.583
Guilt happened.

29:17.583 --> 29:20.083
Your crazy sister, huh?

29:20.083 --> 29:22.917
I didn't make it to
her husband's funeral last year.

29:22.917 --> 29:24.750
And I am
in the neighborhood.

29:24.750 --> 29:27.000
-How long you plan to stay?
-[Saul] Couple days,

29:27.000 --> 29:28.792
or until we murder each other,
whichever comes first.

29:28.792 --> 29:32.208
I gotta say, you picked
an odd time for it.

29:32.208 --> 29:33.750
I'm just about to go in
and brief Keane.

29:33.750 --> 29:36.041
[Saul]
What are you gonna say?

29:36.041 --> 29:38.125
That we're still
developing the intel.

29:38.125 --> 29:40.417
Sounds right. 'Bout time
you learned to stand

29:40.417 --> 29:44.166
on your own two feet anyway.
-I'm hanging up now.

29:44.166 --> 29:44.750
[cellphone clicks]

29:44.750 --> 29:46.667
[man] Thank you, sir.

29:46.667 --> 29:49.834
[indistinct conversations]

29:58.000 --> 30:00.750
[man] Yes, sir, I understand...
[continues indistinctly]

30:00.750 --> 30:04.458
[indistinct conversations]

30:04.458 --> 30:05.875
[door opens]

30:05.875 --> 30:08.333
[indistinct conversations
continue]

30:08.333 --> 30:09.917
Sir. This way.

30:14.500 --> 30:16.333
[door closes]
-[Dar] Madame?

30:16.333 --> 30:17.917
Sit, please.

30:19.959 --> 30:24.000
I understand you're going to
brief me on Abu Dhabi.

30:24.000 --> 30:25.166
That's correct.

30:25.166 --> 30:28.000
And I assume The President's
been briefed.

30:29.125 --> 30:30.792
He has. Last night.

30:30.792 --> 30:34.333
Not by me, but yes,
he's up to speed.

30:34.333 --> 30:37.917
Rob's not going anywhere if
that's what you're waiting for.

30:37.917 --> 30:40.542
You two broke bread
on this subject already.

30:40.542 --> 30:43.333
[glass clinks]

30:43.333 --> 30:44.959
Where's Mr. Berenson?

30:44.959 --> 30:46.875
He's still in the field.

30:46.875 --> 30:48.834
I wanna talk to him
when he gets back.

30:48.834 --> 30:51.500
-If you wish.
-[scoffs] I wish.

30:51.500 --> 30:52.375
[pitcher clatters]

30:52.375 --> 30:55.041
I hate to be the bearer
of bad news.

30:55.041 --> 30:59.792
It appears Iran is violating
the nuclear agreement.

30:59.792 --> 31:01.625
How?

31:01.625 --> 31:04.834
By pursuing a parallel program
in North Korea.

31:04.834 --> 31:06.458
"Appears to be."

31:06.458 --> 31:08.500
The evidence is
more than credible.

31:08.500 --> 31:10.208
Saul calls it conclusive.

31:10.208 --> 31:12.583
Mr. Berenson does.

31:13.834 --> 31:15.208
Yes.

31:15.208 --> 31:18.875
How soon before they actually
have a weapon?

31:18.875 --> 31:21.417
Well, as you're aware,
the North Koreans already do.

31:21.417 --> 31:24.208
The issue now is compatibility.

31:24.208 --> 31:27.583
That is, pairing
the existing warheads

31:27.583 --> 31:29.708
with Iranian ballistic missiles.

31:31.542 --> 31:34.041
Motherfuckers. [sighs]

31:34.041 --> 31:35.375
Who else knows about this?

31:35.375 --> 31:37.291
The Israelis, of course.
The British.

31:37.291 --> 31:38.750
Jesus. Just how big
does this club get?

31:38.750 --> 31:41.375
That's up to the President.

31:41.375 --> 31:44.083
The question is, what's he
going to do about it?

31:46.208 --> 31:48.708
Okay, what would you do?

31:48.708 --> 31:50.000
Call the Iranians out?

31:51.875 --> 31:53.875
I would. Yes.

31:53.875 --> 31:57.083
I'd also impose
snapback sanctions,

31:57.083 --> 31:59.750
sail the Fifth Fleet into
the Strait of Hormuz,

31:59.750 --> 32:01.166
stop all this
accommodating the enemy.

32:01.166 --> 32:04.000
Is that what you're advising
the President to do?

32:04.000 --> 32:07.792
I'm not advising him
to do anything.

32:07.792 --> 32:08.625
My job is to present
intelligence,

32:08.625 --> 32:11.333
not recommend policy.

32:11.333 --> 32:12.500
Unless you're asked.

32:12.500 --> 32:14.417
That's right.

32:16.000 --> 32:18.959
Well, you can guess how I feel
about your advice.

32:18.959 --> 32:21.083
I'm an old spy, Madame.
I trust old friends.

32:21.083 --> 32:22.875
New ones? Not so much.

32:24.208 --> 32:27.041
Well, I'm gonna try
not to take that personally.

32:27.708 --> 32:29.875
That's not what I meant.

32:29.875 --> 32:31.542
I hope not.

32:31.542 --> 32:33.166
Otherwise, you should feel free
to ask the Director

32:33.166 --> 32:37.208
for someone you're
more comfortable with.

32:42.291 --> 32:46.875
You know what? I don't think so.
I think I'll stick with you.

32:49.542 --> 32:52.750
As you wish.

32:52.750 --> 32:55.959
I wish.

32:57.125 --> 33:00.166
[telephone ringing in distance,
indistinct conversations]

33:00.166 --> 33:02.125
-Hey, Carrie.
-Hi. Is Reda in yet?

33:02.125 --> 33:04.708
Haven't seen him. Some flowers
came for you, though.

33:04.708 --> 33:06.125
Flowers? From Mr. During?

33:06.125 --> 33:08.125
Don't know.
They're in your office.

33:08.125 --> 33:11.083
[indistinct conversations
continue]

33:15.625 --> 33:16.875
[envelope rustles]

33:21.166 --> 33:22.750
[telephone rings in distance]
-[woman] Good morning.

33:22.750 --> 33:26.041
[woman speaks indistinctly]

33:26.834 --> 33:28.792
[cellphone chirps]

33:28.792 --> 33:31.667
[touchscreen chirping]

33:31.667 --> 33:33.667
[Conlin] Did he agree
to meet our guy?

33:33.667 --> 33:35.250
-[Saad] He won't do it.
-[Conlin] Work him harder.

33:35.250 --> 33:37.708
-Come on, Conlin.
-You wanna finish your time?

33:37.708 --> 33:39.667
You know I don't.

33:39.667 --> 33:41.500
You gotta push him
to meet Hafiz.

33:41.500 --> 33:43.417
I'm -- I'm telling you,
he flat out refused.

33:43.417 --> 33:47.750
[Conlin] Were you wired up
when he said all that?

33:47.750 --> 33:49.041
[Saad] Well, like always.

33:49.041 --> 33:51.166
[Conlin]
Delete the conversation.

33:51.166 --> 33:53.291
-[Saad] What'd you say?
-[Conlin] You heard me.

33:53.291 --> 33:56.291
-[Conline] Delete the recording.
[cellphone chirps]

33:57.083 --> 33:59.792
You're really something,
Mathison.

33:59.792 --> 34:02.041
I gotta hand it to you.

34:02.041 --> 34:04.875
You are a dog
with a fucking bone.

34:04.875 --> 34:06.375
Your own informant tells you
the kid is harmless.

34:06.375 --> 34:09.917
And what do you do? You just
keep pushing and pushing.

34:09.917 --> 34:12.291
-Who's the one with the bone?
-He was on the brink.

34:12.291 --> 34:14.875
Not even close. Even if
he was, when did we start

34:14.875 --> 34:17.542
arresting people for crimes
they might commit?

34:17.542 --> 34:19.458
Somewhere between 9/11
and Orlando.

34:19.458 --> 34:21.834
Is that also when we started
fabricating evidence

34:21.834 --> 34:22.917
and obstructing justice?

34:22.917 --> 34:27.083
[scoffs] Look...I don't know
where you got that tape,

34:27.083 --> 34:27.708
but it ain't gonna hold up.

34:27.708 --> 34:31.000
I'll take my chances.

34:32.583 --> 34:34.125
What do you want?

34:34.125 --> 34:34.834
All charges dropped.

34:34.834 --> 34:38.083
Ha. Are you high?

34:38.083 --> 34:40.041
Sekou Bah cleared and released
by tomorrow morning,

34:40.041 --> 34:42.792
or this goes to
the Attorney General.

34:45.417 --> 34:49.583
[telephone ringing,
indistinct conversations]

34:49.583 --> 34:54.417
[engine revving]

34:55.917 --> 34:59.083
[engine continues revving]

35:00.333 --> 35:02.708
[child shouts indistinctly,
car approaches]

35:04.125 --> 35:06.166
[child shouts indistinctly]

35:06.166 --> 35:09.834
[dog barking in distance,
engine idling]

35:09.834 --> 35:10.291
[car door closes]

35:12.250 --> 35:14.250
-Saul.
-[chuckles]

35:14.250 --> 35:15.959
Been too long.

35:15.959 --> 35:19.750
I'll admit, I was surprised
to hear from you.

35:19.750 --> 35:21.583
I should've come
when Moshe died.

35:21.583 --> 35:24.125
Come.

35:24.125 --> 35:28.041
We'll have a meal,
then we can talk.

35:28.041 --> 35:29.166
This way.

35:29.166 --> 35:30.792
I remember.

35:30.792 --> 35:34.417
A lot more houses since
the last time I was here.

35:34.417 --> 35:37.333
We've grown.
Almost tripled in size.

35:40.125 --> 35:41.417
View's the same.

35:41.417 --> 35:42.792
Moshe chose this spot

35:42.792 --> 35:45.000
so the Arabs could see us
every day

35:45.000 --> 35:48.000
and know we're never leaving.

35:48.000 --> 35:50.959
I remember that, too.

35:50.959 --> 35:54.834
[insects chirping]

35:56.208 --> 36:00.625
[Dorit] That's Daniel.
His 7th birthday.

36:03.333 --> 36:05.250
That's Jacob,
Dabi and Rebecca's third son.

36:05.250 --> 36:07.792
-[Saul] Mm.
-[Dorit] He's 6 now.

36:07.792 --> 36:10.000
-Looks like his father.
-[chuckles]

36:10.000 --> 36:11.625
He's always getting
into trouble,

36:11.625 --> 36:13.500
so naturally,
he's my favorite.

36:13.500 --> 36:16.708
[distant rapid gunfire]

36:16.708 --> 36:17.875
Does that bother you?

36:17.875 --> 36:20.000
I don't hear it anymore.

36:20.000 --> 36:22.000
-Now, Saul...
[dogs barking in distance]

36:22.000 --> 36:24.375
Tell me about Mira.

36:24.375 --> 36:26.000
What happened?

36:26.000 --> 36:27.041
[dogs continue barking
in distance]

36:27.041 --> 36:30.000
What happens between people.

36:32.500 --> 36:34.000
I made promises
and didn't keep them.

36:34.000 --> 36:36.583
She did the same.

36:38.458 --> 36:40.500
I'm sorry.

36:40.500 --> 36:43.542
Seems like
a million years ago.

36:43.542 --> 36:45.542
And there's been
no one since?

36:46.667 --> 36:49.208
No.

36:52.208 --> 36:53.417
[inhales sharply]

36:53.417 --> 36:56.041
I wish you could stay
for Shabbat.

36:56.041 --> 36:58.834
Both boys come with their wives
and all the children.

36:58.834 --> 37:00.959
Maybe next time.

37:03.375 --> 37:06.834
I tell them stories
about Indiana,

37:06.834 --> 37:09.542
being one of eight Jewish
families in the entire town.

37:09.542 --> 37:10.708
[chuckles]

37:10.708 --> 37:12.625
How you were my protector.

37:12.625 --> 37:15.917
[laughs] Hey, even when you
didn't want my protection.

37:15.917 --> 37:17.959
[chuckles]

37:17.959 --> 37:21.166
We were so close.

37:22.041 --> 37:24.291
After I married Moshe,

37:24.291 --> 37:26.083
you practically disappeared
from my life.

37:26.083 --> 37:28.333
I visited when I could.

37:28.333 --> 37:29.458
Afternoon now and then.

37:33.208 --> 37:35.583
Moshe and I saw things
differently.

37:35.583 --> 37:36.708
He was my husband.

37:36.708 --> 37:39.333
You could've tried to
understand his point of view.

37:39.333 --> 37:40.291
Did he try
to understand mine?

37:40.291 --> 37:42.291
You could've bent a little
for my sake.

37:42.291 --> 37:44.834
There's no bending
with a fanatic.

37:50.792 --> 37:51.542
After you met him...

37:53.917 --> 37:56.458
You changed.

37:56.458 --> 37:59.542
Moshe opened my eyes

37:59.542 --> 38:03.083
to the false life that mother
and father had us living --

38:03.083 --> 38:05.458
exchanging Christmas presents
with the neighbors,

38:05.458 --> 38:07.000
doing everything we could

38:07.000 --> 38:09.041
not to offend anyone
with our Jewishness.

38:09.041 --> 38:11.792
Moshe made me proud
to be a Jew.

38:11.792 --> 38:13.792
He turned you
against your family.

38:15.375 --> 38:18.166
He brought you to live
in a place that's not yours,

38:18.166 --> 38:20.417
where you don't belong.

38:22.458 --> 38:23.708
[exhales] Please, Saul,
let's not do this.

38:23.708 --> 38:27.500
Haven't you driven enough people
from their homes already?

38:27.500 --> 38:28.125
[sighs]

38:28.125 --> 38:30.458
Bulldoze their villages,

38:30.458 --> 38:33.667
seized their property under laws
they had no part in makin'?

38:34.708 --> 38:37.625
This land was promised
to Abraham.

38:37.625 --> 38:39.583
Ah, yes. Promise.

38:41.625 --> 38:44.708
A covenant with God made
thousands of years ago.

38:44.708 --> 38:46.083
[sighs]

38:46.083 --> 38:48.917
Doesn't that strike you
as a form of insanity?

38:48.917 --> 38:50.458
[exhales]

38:50.458 --> 38:54.125
You don't understand, Saul.
You never have.

38:54.125 --> 38:58.166
I love the life
that God has given me.

38:58.166 --> 39:00.208
How can you love
making enemies?

39:00.208 --> 39:03.166
How can you love knowing that
your very presence here

39:03.166 --> 39:06.333
makes peace less possible?

39:07.125 --> 39:10.375
I have a family,
a community,

39:10.375 --> 39:15.208
a life filled with faith
and purpose.

39:15.208 --> 39:19.750
Saul...what do you have?

39:32.250 --> 39:34.208
[gate clanks]
-Hey.

39:34.208 --> 39:36.333
[horns honks in distance,
vehicles passing]

39:37.583 --> 39:40.291
-What is this, a group home?
-Come on, let's go.

39:40.291 --> 39:41.500
What do you want, baby?
You wanna party?

39:41.500 --> 39:45.208
No, I wanna see
your boyfriend, Tommy.

39:45.208 --> 39:48.792
Oh, well...he's not gonna
give you your money back.

39:48.792 --> 39:51.125
I don't want my money back.

39:51.125 --> 39:53.875
Then what?

39:53.875 --> 39:56.333
That's between him and me.

39:56.333 --> 39:58.208
What do you say you and I
go eat some Thai instead?

39:58.208 --> 40:00.583
Just give me the keys.

40:03.041 --> 40:05.375
[sighs heavily]

40:06.333 --> 40:10.208
[horn honking in distance]

40:10.208 --> 40:11.250
[car door closes, engine starts]

40:11.250 --> 40:15.166
[train tracks rattling]

40:18.208 --> 40:20.125
[indistinct conversations]

40:20.125 --> 40:22.417
[engine rumbling]

40:22.417 --> 40:25.542
[engine turns off, horn honks]

40:25.542 --> 40:28.250
Baby, don't do this.

40:28.250 --> 40:31.708
-Please?
-Which one is his?

40:31.708 --> 40:33.875
I can get you what you need,
and we can have a good time.

40:33.875 --> 40:36.834
Tommy...

40:36.834 --> 40:39.250
[voice breaking]
He will fuck you up.

40:41.417 --> 40:44.417
Now are you going to tell me
or do I have to start...

40:48.166 --> 40:51.750
...knocking on doors?

40:55.583 --> 40:57.583
Number 18.

40:57.583 --> 40:59.250
Thank you.

40:59.250 --> 41:02.583
[seat belt unlocks, clatters]

41:04.834 --> 41:05.792
[man shouting indistinctly]

41:09.333 --> 41:13.333
[vehicles passing]

41:18.250 --> 41:21.125
[muffled conversation]

41:21.125 --> 41:22.250
[knocks on door]

41:22.250 --> 41:24.083
[Tommy] Yo, hold on!

41:29.917 --> 41:32.250
[lock clicking]

41:33.625 --> 41:34.458
Clarice ain't here.

41:34.458 --> 41:37.667
Oh, I'm not looking
for Clarice.

41:37.667 --> 41:39.625
What then?

41:41.166 --> 41:43.125
Business.

41:49.708 --> 41:52.125
[siren wailing in distance,
door locks]

41:52.125 --> 41:56.583
I saw a video of you on YouTube,
gettin' gassed in the shower.

41:56.583 --> 41:59.917
-Ah, I haven't seen it.
-Yeah, you lived it, I guess.

41:59.917 --> 42:02.000
[gun thuds]
-[sniffs] You wanna sit?

42:02.000 --> 42:03.750
No, I'm good.

42:03.750 --> 42:06.333
Hey, man,
if I knew who you was,

42:06.333 --> 42:07.834
I never would've
knocked you out.

42:07.834 --> 42:10.750
-Ah.
-But you just kept dancin'.

42:10.750 --> 42:12.500
Yeah, I hear music sometimes.

42:12.500 --> 42:14.834
-[chuckles]
[train passing]

42:14.834 --> 42:17.583
-How much for your gun?
-What?

42:17.583 --> 42:19.333
I-I wanna buy your gun.
How much?

42:19.333 --> 42:21.625
It's not for sale.

42:21.625 --> 42:25.375
I figure you paid $700 for it.
I'll give you $1,500.

42:27.125 --> 42:29.542
$2,000.

42:29.542 --> 42:31.041
[exhales deeply]

42:31.041 --> 42:33.166
Okay, $2,000.

42:33.166 --> 42:34.291
Uh, with a free bump.

42:34.291 --> 42:38.166
[chuckles] Deal.

42:42.792 --> 42:46.708
Oh! Jesus Christ!
What the fuck, man?!

42:46.708 --> 42:48.917
Fuckin' spaz.

42:48.917 --> 42:50.250
♪ tense music ♪

42:50.250 --> 42:51.500
[smack]
-[grunts]

42:51.500 --> 42:54.583
Fuck, man! Aah!

42:54.583 --> 42:56.875
[groans]

42:56.875 --> 42:59.041
So...

42:59.041 --> 43:00.792
-That's the $2,000 I owe you.
-[Groans]

43:00.792 --> 43:04.500
Less the $2,000 you stole
from me, leaves what?

43:04.500 --> 43:06.583
How much I owe you now?

43:06.583 --> 43:09.333
Z-zero. N-nothing.

43:09.333 --> 43:11.291
You're fucking right.

43:11.291 --> 43:12.875
[groans]

43:12.875 --> 43:16.291
[siren wailing in distance,
indistinct conversations]

43:16.291 --> 43:17.834
[horn honks in distance]

43:20.417 --> 43:23.417
♪ light jazz music ♪

43:23.417 --> 43:26.542
[indistinct conversations]

43:26.542 --> 43:29.250
[man] Hi, Carrie.
Good evening.

43:29.250 --> 43:32.417
[water spraying]

43:32.417 --> 43:34.291
[dishes clatters]

43:34.291 --> 43:36.291
Phone.

43:38.583 --> 43:39.583
You know,
I don't know your name.

43:39.583 --> 43:42.667
-Thoms.
-Thoms, I'm Carrie.

43:42.667 --> 43:44.500
It's nice to see you again,
Carrie.

43:47.875 --> 43:49.708
Carrie,
thank you for coming.

43:49.708 --> 43:51.750
Of course.

43:51.750 --> 43:53.417
Have a seat.

43:58.708 --> 44:02.125
I have been coming here
for years.

44:02.125 --> 44:05.125
Aaron proposed to me
in this restaurant.

44:05.125 --> 44:08.792
Not here.
Out there, but...

44:08.792 --> 44:11.792
[whispers] I won the place
in the divorce.

44:11.792 --> 44:13.083
[chuckles]

44:13.083 --> 44:15.959
It's almost true. He got
the house in Lake Placid,

44:15.959 --> 44:19.959
and I got exclusive rights
to the steak au poivre.

44:19.959 --> 44:22.500
-Wine?
-Oh, not for me, thanks.

44:22.500 --> 44:24.291
Although, I could use it.
[chuckles]

44:24.291 --> 44:25.792
Right. Forgot. Sorry.

44:25.792 --> 44:27.667
No, no, it's fine.

44:27.667 --> 44:30.417
Let's get business out
of the way before we order.

44:30.417 --> 44:31.542
Tell me.

44:31.542 --> 44:34.333
This question with Iran,

44:34.333 --> 44:36.708
it could get me stuck
in the starting blocks.

44:36.708 --> 44:38.041
I had a visit from Dar Adal.

44:38.041 --> 44:42.667
He outlined some very unpleasant
options in the event

44:42.667 --> 44:46.291
that Iran has found a way
around the IAEA inspections.

44:46.291 --> 44:48.625
And have they?

44:48.625 --> 44:50.333
Apparently,
that parallel program's

44:50.333 --> 44:52.542
underway in North Korea.

44:52.542 --> 44:53.750
Saul Berenson said this.

44:53.750 --> 44:55.583
Mr. Berenson wasn't
in the meeting,

44:55.583 --> 44:59.166
but his report called
the evidence conclusive.

44:59.166 --> 45:02.834
Really? He used that word,
"conclusive"?

45:02.834 --> 45:05.500
According to Mr. Adal,
he did.

45:05.500 --> 45:07.041
So you didn't actually see
the report yourself.

45:07.041 --> 45:09.959
No.

45:09.959 --> 45:12.583
-Ask for it. Read it.
-Why?

45:12.583 --> 45:15.792
Intelligence officers usually
hedge their bets. It's...

45:15.792 --> 45:16.792
It's kind of an art form.

45:16.792 --> 45:21.375
We use phrases like
"best judgment,"

45:21.375 --> 45:23.417
or, I don't know,
"degree of confidence."

45:23.417 --> 45:25.625
That's why when George Tenet
said "slam dunk,"

45:25.625 --> 45:27.291
we all sat up
in our chairs.

45:27.291 --> 45:28.041
Hmm.

45:28.041 --> 45:31.041
The other thing
you need to do,

45:31.041 --> 45:32.708
if you don't
mind me saying...

45:32.708 --> 45:35.708
-Please, it's why you're here.
-Reach out to President Morse

45:35.708 --> 45:38.041
and make sure he knows
that you're unconvinced.

45:38.041 --> 45:41.333
That way, whether the Iranians
are cheating on the deal or not,

45:41.333 --> 45:43.667
no decision gets made
without your input.

45:43.667 --> 45:45.417
[Keane] I will.
I'll do that tonight.

45:45.417 --> 45:46.667
And thank you.

45:46.667 --> 45:48.583
You know they say
that presidents

45:48.583 --> 45:50.041
don't make new friends.

45:50.041 --> 45:55.333
I'm hoping we're the exception
that proves the...

45:55.333 --> 45:57.667
♪ dramatic music ♪

45:57.667 --> 46:01.375
[dog barking in distance]

46:01.375 --> 46:04.458
♪♪♪

46:09.792 --> 46:13.667
[cellphone vibrating]

46:34.750 --> 46:37.875
♪♪♪

46:41.750 --> 46:43.834
[lock turns]

46:53.750 --> 46:56.834
♪♪♪

47:07.625 --> 47:11.542
[dog barking in distance]

47:14.625 --> 47:16.208
[door clanks]

47:16.208 --> 47:19.083
♪♪♪

47:35.000 --> 47:36.166
[vehicle approaches]

47:41.834 --> 47:44.250
[car door closes]
-[man] Get down.

47:44.250 --> 47:45.417
[engine idling]

47:45.417 --> 47:47.125
I said get down.

48:05.708 --> 48:07.750
[shifts gears, turns off engine]

48:21.542 --> 48:23.417
[door opens]

48:25.041 --> 48:26.375
[door closes]

48:29.542 --> 48:32.625
♪♪♪

48:49.583 --> 48:53.417
♪♪♪

49:04.750 --> 49:07.834
♪♪♪
